  <p align="left">    This update is a bit longer than usual but it has some important information on dates and processes for next year and we want you all to know well in advance.</p>
  <p><strong>Bible Reading</strong></p>
  <p>Tony Campolo (together with people like Jim Wallis and Brian McLaren) is highlighting the need for Christians to get more familiar with the teachings of Jesus. To let our lifestyles be determined by His words. All the more vital then that, as a mission, we stay true to our value of being Jesus centred, and our practice of reading the gospels. Therefore, the readings for next 3 months are: </p>
  <ul>
    <li>October - Gospel of John </li>
    <li>November - Isaiah (cos it contains the most prophecies of Jesus life) </li>
    <li>December - Gospel of Luke (who celebrates women more than the other gospels) </li>
  </ul>  <p><strong>Project Serve </strong></p>
  <p>Gus <a href="mailto:g.row@yfc.org.nz">g.row@yfc.org.nz</a> has prepared a proposal (see Project Serve proposal below below) on how we can make PS far more central to our mission. All over the place, Christians and non-Christians are looking for ways to do something of significance. Already there are 4 travel agencies in NZ focused on offering &quot;service&quot; holidays. YFC needs to be pushing the boundaries on this. So the proposal calls us to more sacrificial action. </p>
  <p><strong>Surge</strong> </p>
  <p>This is the replacement for CTC. As previously stated it will be in Whanganui, April 19-22, so ring those dates in indelible ink. Start thinking and talking now, about how you can get members, associates, helpers kids (all ages) to this event. It will set the tone of our mission for years to come. There'll be more details next month but for now - plan to be there! Glen is coordinating this <a href="mailto:g.bennett@yfc.org.nz">g.bennett@yfc.org.nz</a>.</p>
  <p><strong>Some items for celebration </strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Nelson and Marlborough Supporters night <a href="mailto:nelson@yfc.org.nz">nelson@yfc.org.nz</a> <a href="mailto:marlborough@yfc.org.nz">marlborough@yfc.org.nz</a> </li>
    <li>Some great stories of significant moments in kids lives at Rock Solid camps around the country.</li>
    <li>Rock Solid discipleship happening in Timaru <a href="mailto:timaru@yfc.org.nz">timaru@yfc.org.nz</a> </li>
    <li> Change the world discipleship group meeting in Wellington <a href="mailto:r.o&#8217;connor@yfc.org.nz">r.o&rsquo;connor@yfc.org.nz</a> </li>
    <li>Samstock in Otago <a href="mailto:r.grant@yfc.org.nz">r.grant@yfc.org.nz </a></li>
  </ul>  <p><strong>Future membership</strong></p>
  <p>We have agreed that we need a better process for determining who is a member, associate, helper etc. Here is how we will work it for 2007.</p>
  <p><em>Purpose</em>. To have a committed group of members who have the YFC DNA. This will probably mean we have fewer members after the next Gathering (currently 56) but more associates. We need to better define associates and helpers. Gus has prepared diagram with three concentric circles and explains this well. The outer circle has many ways into being a helper, less ways to the next circle to being an associate and only one way into being a member.</p>
  <p align="center"><img src="20061004/circles.gif" width="550" height="400"> </p>
  <p><em>Process</em>. We hold a North and South Island weekend for the ethos of membership. This will go from Saturday noon (starting with lunch) and finish after lunch on Sunday. Anyone who wants to be considered a member after the next Gathering must attend one of these.</p>
  <p>The Wanganui Surge weekend (19 &ndash; 22 April) is the work weekend with 2 &ndash; 3 times of reflection, debriefing etc of those who want to be members after the next Gathering (they will have already attended one of the ethos weekends). Again, attendance at this will be necessary to be a member after the next Gathering.</p>
  <p>We will more clearly define associate membership and the practices expected and will have a member coordinate and communicate regularly with these people.</p>
  <p><strong>Dates</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Feb 10 &ndash; 11 Ethos weekend (North Island). Venue to be advised</li>
    <li> Feb 24 &ndash; 25 Ethos weekend (South Island) Venue to be advised</li>
    <li>April 19 &ndash; 22 Wanganui weekend (Surge)</li>
    <li>April 30th All those who want to be members are told yes or no (from Gathering onwards).</li>
    <li>April 30th All associates informed yes or no and regular contact starts.</li>
    <li>June 2 - 3 Gathering (Queens Birthday weekend) this will be for members only. Will probably be in Wellington.</li>
    <li>August Converge South Island focusing on Associates and helpers. Members there to serve them. (actual dates to be confirmed in the next month)</li>
    <li>August Converge North Island focusing on Associates and helpers. Members there to serve them. (actual dates to be confirmed in the next month)</li>
    <li>2008 Same basic time frame except there will be no ethos weekends and gathering can change to best date for members</li>
  </ul>  <p><strong>Finally</strong></p>
